40|$|Applying a time-discrete {{investment}} {{model and}} a setting with an entry and an exit option and cash flow uncertainty {{we present a}} dynamic analysis {{of the impact of}} various <b>loss</b> <b>offset</b> regimes on risky investment timing decisions. We find that a tax system with <b>loss</b> <b>offset</b> restrictions will not distort timing decisions if the investor can exit the project. By contrast, in a setting without exit flexibility a tax discrimination against losses can cause paradoxical effects. In that respect, we analytically identify conditions for higher taxes to increase investors' propensity to choose early investment and hence accelerate entrepreneurial investment...|$|E
