25|$|Huntington's {{involvement}} with urban rail was intimately tied to his {{real estate development}} operations. Real estate development was so lucrative for Huntington and SP that they could use the Red Car as a loss leader. However, by 1920, {{when most of the}} company's holdings had been developed, their major income source began to deplete. Many rural passenger lines were unprofitable, with <b>losses</b> <b>offset</b> by revenue generated from passenger lines in populated corridors and from freight operations. The least-used Red Car lines were converted to cheaper bus routes as early as 1925.|$|R
